    • getPartition

      public double[] getPartition​(int n)
      Computes the partition of the Gamma distribution into n categories. The partition is defined by the percentage points for 1/n, 2/n, ..., 1-1/n.
      Parameters:
      n - number of partitions: must be at least 1
      Returns:
      array of n-1 elements corresponding to the percentage points i/n i=1,...,n-1

    • getPartitionMeans

      public double[] getPartitionMeans​(int n)
      Takes the partition of the Gamma distribution into n categories. The partition is defined by the percentage points for 1/n, 2/n, ..., 1-1/n. Computes the mean value within each interval [i/n, (i+1)/n] for i=0..n-1
      Parameters:
      n - number of partitions: supposed to be at least 1
      Returns:
      array of n elements corresponding to the means within the partitions

    • getPartitionMeans

      public double[] getPartitionMeans​(int n, double[] partition)
      Takes the partition of the Gamma distribution into n categories. The partition is defined by the percentage points for 1/n, 2/n, ..., 1-1/n. Computes the mean value within each interval [i/n, (i+1)/n] for i=0..n-1
      Parameters:
      n - number of partitions: supposed to be at least 1
      partition - if not null, then this must be an array of length at least n-1, where the partition boundaries are saved (result of getPartition)
      Returns:
      array of n elements corresponding to the means within the partitions
